Wed. Aug. 5th from 4:00 p.m.- 5:00 p.m. and 7:00 p.m.-8:00 p.m.
Thu. Aug. 6th from 8:00 a.m. - 9:00 a.m.
Mon. Aug. 10th from 7:00 p.m.-8:00 p.m.

Best wishes,
Beth

Strong Foundations PTO
May 29 at 10:53 AM ¬∑

Strong Foundations is going to have a Scholastic Summer Read-A-Palooza Virtual Book Fair. It will run from now until September 4th. All book orders over $25 will receive F*R*E*E shipping.

The school will earn 25% of the book sales in scholastic dollars. The scholastic dollars we earn buy supplies for the benefit of the entire school, like wiggle chairs and classroom books and activities for after care. There are also great activity kits and workbooks offered by scholastic, which make great gifts. Please share the link to the book fair with family, friends and neighbors.

The spring book fair sold over $900 in books and earned the school over $200 in scholastic dollars. The goal for the summer would be to sell 250 books or more!

Here is the link for the Virtual Summer Book Fair:
https://bookfairs.scholastic.com/bookfairs/cptoolkit/homepage.do?method=homepage&url=strongfoundationschtrsch1

Please know that the books do take about two weeks to ship as there are limited individuals working in the warehouse.

Thank you so much for your continued support.

post_text:
Dear SFCS Families,

It's hard to believe, but the end of the school year is less than a month away! We wanted to let you know about some very important end of year dates.

The last instructional day will be Wed. June 10th.

We will have three days for all technology and materials to be returned: June 11th, 12th, and 15th from 7am-5pm. Graduation will be held on June 16th. More details to come later.

Please bring all technology and charging cords back to us in good condition. We will be monitoring returned items to be sure they are in the same condition as when you received them.

Middle School students also borrowed novels for Language Arts. Please bring those back as well.

If your students have any library books that belong to Strong Foundations, please be sure to bring those back also.

Thank you very much!

post_text:
Hello, SFCS Families,

Thank you so much for your support, for your dedication at home, and for your kind encouragement. For several weeks I have been talking with staff and families about how everyone is doing while I tried to decide whether to just keep working through April vacation or whether to have us take the scheduled break that week.

We will be taking our April vacation as expected. My hope is that families and staff can use that time to relax and come back refreshed for the last six weeks of school.

Schools across the state seem evenly split regarding whether they will take the scheduled break. This approach seemed like the best approach for us.



Thank you again!
Beth McClure, Principal

post_text:
Dear SFCS Families,

As I mentioned earlier, this is a rapidly changing situation. Our Board of Trustees and I met today, and we have decided that it makes the most sense to close school beginning on Monday. We will start remote learning on Wednesday.

All teachers will be at school preparing their online instruction to begin on Wednesday. We will be spending the next two days putting the process into place.

We will have iPads available for use at home if a student does not have a device. If you need to borrow an iPad, please let us know. We will send out an email telling you when one will be available.

Your child's learning and safety is very important to us. We will be updating you as necessary. Thank you for your kind understanding during this very unusual time.

Sincerely,

Beth McClure

shared_text:
Strong Foundations PTO
January 27 at 11:44 PM ¬∑

It‚Äôs Girl Scout Cookie time! Why not join String Foundations Charter School in their Random Act of Kindness, Cookies for a Cause!
Want to help Strong Foundations Girl Scout Troup while at the same time do something nice and avoid those cookie calories?

Strong Foundations Charter School in Pembroke, NH is on a mission to purchase as many boxes of Girl Scout Cookies as possible, to send to our soldiers overseas.
With all the challenges our soldiers face being overseas and away from home, they could really use a "sweet" pick me up! If you would like to donate to this amazing cause, please drop your monetary donation off at the Strong Foundations Charter School office. Girl Scout Cookies are $5 per box. Cash or check donations will be accepted to be used toward the purchase of the cookies from the Strong Foundations Girl Scout Troop. Any questions, please call Christine at 603-225-2715.
Donations are being accepted NOW through January 31st!!! Let‚Äôs show our military how much we appreciate them!

We, at Strong Foundations, are going to be hosting our very first "cookies for a cause" event!!

It‚Äôs Girl Scout Cookie time! Want to help our SFCS Girl Scout Troup while at the same time do something nice and avoid those cookie calories?

We are asking, if you wish to participate, for your help to get as many boxes of Girl Scout Cookies as possible, to send to our soldiers overseas.

With all the challenges our soldiers face being overseas and away from home, they could really use a "sweet" pick me up! It would be easiest to bring us a cash or check donation to be used toward the purchase of the cookies from our very own SFCS Girl Scout Troop. Please contact Kacie Segelstrom or Christine Bouffard directly with any questions.

We will be taking donations starting NOW right up until January 31st!!!

Thank you very much for helping our first ever "cookies for a cause" event be a success!

post_text: With winter weather on the way, a reminder of how to find out information regarding delays or snow days. This post is pinned at the top of this page as well.
shared_text:
Strong Foundations Charter School
November 15, 2018 at 9:31 AM ¬∑

If we have a delay or closing due to weather, we will post that information to WMUR by approximately 5:30am. We will also use our emergency phone notification system (call/text). Please do not solely rely on this Facebook page for this information, as things can change and there may be a delay in getting this page updated. SFCS will be listed separately from any other district, as we make the decision on our own. Hot lunch will still be available if Pembroke decides to close on a day we remain open.

Depending on where you live, weather near you may be very different. If the travel conditions in your area are dangerous, you can let us know that you are keeping your child home for that reason by calling the office. We make our decisions based on our local conditions, and we respect that it may be different where you live.

May 4, 2019 at 12:24 PM ¬∑

The Spring Concert is quickly approaching! We need your help to fill our baskets for the raffle!

The themes are listed below!

If you are able, please send in an item with your child for their class basket in accordance with their class theme. There will be a box located in their classroom for the collections or you may bring them to the office. Items valued at approximately $5. The deadline for donations will be MAY 6th, 2019!

Here are the class themes:
Readiness: Crayola
1st Grade: Fun in the Sun
2nd Grade: Ice-cream
3rd Grade: Chocolate
4th Grade: Coffee
5th Grade: BBQ
6th Grade: Movie Night
7th Grade: Game Night
8th Grade: Gift Cards

The completed theme baskets will be displayed along the entrance to the concert in order to help you decide on one, some, or all of which you wish to take your chance. Tickets will be available for purchase before you settle in for the show. The winner will be drawn at the concert during intermission!

If you are able, please send in an item with your child for their class basket in accordance with their class theme. There will be a box located in their classroom for the collections or you may bring them to the office. Items valued at approximately $5. The deadline for donations will be MAY 6th, 2019!

Here are the class themes:
Readiness: Crayola
1st Grade: Fun in the Sun
2nd Grade: Ice-cream
3rd Grade: Chocolate
4th Grade: Coffee
5th Grade: BBQ
6th Grade: Movie Night
7th Grade: Game Night
8th Grade: Gift Cards

The completed theme baskets will be displayed along the entrance to the concert in order to help you decide on one, some, or all of which you wish to take your chance. Tickets will be available for purchase before you settle in for the show. The winner will be drawn at the concert during intermission!

post_text:
Dyslexia or "Dysteachia"?

How One School District Used The Ôªø"Switch" Framework To Improve Services to Students With Dyslexia

Thursday, April 4, 2019
Nashua Community College
505 Amherst St, Nashua, NH
7:00 - 9:00 pm

Free and open to the public

Dr. Sara Stetson is an award-winning university professor with 20 years of experience. She has taught graduate courses in learning disabilities and reading, cognition, assessment and diagnosis, diversity, UDL/technology integration, and given guest lectures on quantitative and qualitative research design. Her primary research interests include learning disabilities,numerical cognition, diversity, and leadership ethics.

Dr. Stetson's educational background includes learning disabilities and reading, school psychology, and leadership and learning. She has worked as a learning disabilities specialist, consulting teacher, school psychologist, special education director, student services administrator, and assistant superintendent.

post_text:
Strong Foundations is an open enrollment public school that does not accept tuition from parents.

Our application period is from January 1st through March 31st. If more students apply than Strong Foundations can accept, a lottery will be conducted for the openings. Students not selected by lottery but wishing to attend will be placed on a waiting list. Students applying after these dates will be placed if there are any open positions. If not, they will be added to the waiting list in the order that their applications are received.

November 15, 2018 at 9:31 AM ¬∑

If we have a delay or closing due to weather, we will post that information to WMUR by approximately 5:30am. We will also use our emergency phone notification system (call/text). Please do not solely rely on this Facebook page for this information, as things can change and there may be a delay in getting this page updated. SFCS will be listed separately from any other district, as we make the decision on our own. Hot lunch will still be available if Pembroke decides to close on a day we remain open.

Depending on where you live, weather near you may be very different. If the travel conditions in your area are dangerous, you can let us know that you are keeping your child home for that reason by calling the office. We make our decisions based on our local conditions, and we respect that it may be different where you live.

post_text:
If we have a delay or closing due to weather, we will post that information to WMUR by approximately 5:30am. We will also use our emergency phone notification system (call/text). Please do not solely rely on this Facebook page for this information, as things can change and there may be a delay in getting this page updated. SFCS will be listed separately from any other district, as we make the decision on our own. Hot lunch will still be available if Pembroke decides to close on a day we remain open.

Depending on where you live, weather near you may be very different. If the travel conditions in your area are dangerous, you can let us know that you are keeping your child home for that reason by calling the office. We make our decisions based on our local conditions, and we respect that it may be different where you live.

***IMPORTANT NOTICE***

Our parking lot will be paved on MONDAY!
We just received word today.
There will be NO SCHOOL on Monday, September 17th!

Please understand that we have been at the mercy of construction and the weather. We sincerely apologize for the short notice!!!

The new parking lot is certainly something to celebrate, as not only will it make for smoother drop-off and pick-up times, but it means we are one step closer to our new building!

Thank you for your understanding and patience!

shared_text:
Strong Foundations PTO
September 9, 2018 at 9:37 AM ¬∑

Our first PTO meeting of the year will be held on Tuesday September 11th at 6pm in our Multi-Purpose room.

Our meetings focus on making our school a great place by supporting teachers, staff and students in many different ways.

We welcome you to come visit our first meeting and see what we are about. We are fortunate to have a wonderful group of parents over the past years that have dedicated their time to our PTO and the outcome has been amazing.

We understand that parents are crazy busy and may not be able to make every meeting. THAT‚ÄôS OK! We are very grateful for those who have taken on roles behind the scenes and at events.

If you would like to be involved, but cannot make it to our meeting this week, please reach out so we can determine ways to have you involved.
